		<technology>
			<technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses xml:lang="en">The future supply routes for spodumene are described in technical reports of operations at the Whabouchi site, Canada and the Central Ostrobothnia region, Finland. While neither Canada nor Finland are among the countries with the largest lithium reserves (USGS, 2021), they represent examples of new lithium supplies that might become exploited in response to increased lithium demand. The average lithium concentration in spodumene at the Whabouchi site is about 0.7% and in Central Ostrobothnia region it is 0.6%. In these future supply routes, concentrated spodumene is directly converted to LiOH⋅H2O without producing Li2CO3 as an intermediate. The datasets representing mining operations in Canada and Finland are based on the technical reports prepared for Nemaska Lithium Inc. (Golder Associates, 2013; Laferri´ere et al., 2012; Nemaska Lithium Inc., 2013; SENES Consultants Ltd., 2013) and Keliber Oy (Keliber Oy, 2020a, b; Sweco, 2016), respectively. Specific data for chemical inputs was not available for the LiOH⋅H2O production unit process (from concentrated spodumene) in the Nemaska Lithium reports. Therefore, the chemical usage in the Keliber Oy reports were used as proxy data when comparing the different lithium supplies.</technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses>
			<technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses xml:lang="zh">加拿大 Whabouchi 矿区和芬兰中部 Ostrobothnia 地区的运营技术报告中描述了未来的闪锌矿供应路线。虽然加拿大和芬兰都不是锂储量最大的国家（美国地质调查局，2021 年），但它们代表了新锂供应的范例，可能会随着锂需求的增加而被开采。Whabouchi矿区的钠长石中平均锂浓度约为0.7%，而在中奥斯特罗布特尼亚地区则为0.6%。在这些未来的供应路线中，浓缩的磷灰石会直接转化为 LiOH⋅H2O，而不会产生 Li2CO3 作为中间产物。代表加拿大和芬兰采矿作业的数据集分别基于为内玛斯卡锂业公司（Golder Associates，2013 年；Laferri´ere 等人，2012 年；内玛斯卡锂业公司，2013 年；SENES 咨询有限公司，2013 年）和 Keliber Oy（Keliber Oy，2020a，b；Sweco，2016 年）编写的技术报告。在内玛斯卡锂业公司的报告中，没有关于锂OH⋅H2O 生产单元工艺（来自浓缩锂辉石）的化学品投入的具体数据。因此，在比较不同的锂供应时，Keliber Oy 报告中的化学品用量被用作替代数据。</technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="en">This dataset pertains to the production of battery-grade lithium hydroxide monohydrate using the lithium sulfate process, which is sourced from Canadian lithium spodumene concentrate. This high-purity chemical is crucial for the manufacture of lithium-ion batteries that are used in various applications, including electric vehicles, portable electronics, and energy storage systems.</technologicalApplicability>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="zh">该数据集涉及使用硫酸锂法生产的电池级单水氢氧化锂，其源自加拿大锂辉石精矿。这种高纯度化学品对于制造不同应用的锂离子电池至关重要，包括电动汽车、便携式电子设备和能源存储系统。</technologicalApplicability>
